HOWTO run tests
---------------

By Txor.


* mmforwarder - Forwards one video and one audio streams.

    1- Generate a suitable video file coded with h264 and pcm_mulaw:
        ffmpeg -i your_media_file.any -map 0:0 -map 0:1 -vcodec libx264 -c:a pcm_mulaw your_media_file.avi       

    2- Generate an SDP file with this command and save it (say audio_param.sdp), remember to change the ports to 6004 and 6006):
        ffmpeg -i your_media_file.avi 

    3- Start the media receiver with our SDP file:
        ffplay audio_param.sdp

    4- Start the test (listening on 5004 nad 5006, sending to 6004 and 6006):
        bin/mmforwarder

    5- Start the media transmitter with our media file:
        ffmpeg -i your_media_file.avi .... -f rtp rtp://127.0.0.1:5004 -f rtp rtp://127.0.0.1:5006

